```
public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    int x = 1;
    while (n != 0) {
        if (n % 3 == 0) {
            x = x * 3;
            n /= 3;
        } else {
            return false;
        }
    }
    if (x == 1) {
        return true;
    } else {
        return false;
    }
}
```

The code uses a loop to iterate through the values of n until it reaches a value of 0. For each iteration, it checks whether the value of n is divisible by 3. If it is, then it multiplies x by 3 and divides n by 3. Otherwise, it returns false. Once n reaches 0, the loop terminates and we can check whether x equals to 1. If so, we return true. Otherwise, we return false.

